    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-09-25T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-09-25T18:00:00-05:00" n="77"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d77">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/1872: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Nanking</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Peck</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-25T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 25, 1931—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>79. Your 68, September 25, 10 a.m. What the Secretary said, on the afternoon of
                    September 22, to the Japanese Ambassador<note n="70" xml:id="d77fn70">For
                        memorandum of conversation in full, see <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_5">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 5</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1931-41v01#pg_8">8</ref>.</note> in this connection was:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“It would seem that the responsibility for determining the course of
                            events with regard to the liquidating of this situation rests largely
                            upon Japan, for the simple reason that Japanese armed forces have seized
                            and are exercising <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> control in South
                            Manchuria.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>You may discreetly inform the inquirer by oral paraphrase.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
